assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: TOYO Corporation provides measurement instruments and technologies in Japan. The company operates in eight segments: ICT; Mechatronics/Noise & Vibration/Sensors; Physics/Energies; EMC & Antenna Systems; Ocean/Defense & Security; Software Quality & Productivity; Life Science/Materials; and Security & Lab Company. The ICT segments offers ultra-high speed IP network performance test solution; high speed packet capture & analysis systems; and autonomous driving measurement solution. The Mechatronics/Noise & Vibration/Sensors segment provides microphones/particle velocity sensors, torque meters/brake systems, real video drive player, and resource/data management software. The Physics/Energies segment offers secondary battery, fuel cell, semiconductor material, and ferroelectric material evaluation systems; charging analyzers/simulators for electric vehicles; and liquid crystal characteristic measurement systems. The EMC & Antenna Systems segment provides RF power amplifiers, EMI test receivers, and hydrogen masers. The Ocean/Defense & Security segment offers multibeam echosounders, acoustic video cameras, underwater and unmanned surface vehicles, sub-bottom profilers, and acoustic positioning systems. The Software Quality & Productivity segment provides software configuration management tools, software reverse engineering tools, web & mobile app testing tools, and software modeling tools. The Life Science/Materials segment offers atomic force and focused ion beam scanning electron microscopes and micro-CT systems. The Security & Lab Company segment provides cyber-threat intelligence & dark web monitoring, and threat intelligence platform. It also offers consulting, technical support, and after sales services, as well as organizes seminars and training courses. The company was formerly known as TOYO Trading Co., Ltd. and changed its name to TOYO Corporation in February 1977. The company was incorporated in 1946 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
